### Summary of the new feature / enhancement

I recently saw a user who wanted to await user input but also intermittently perform a background task. The current solution for this is something like this:

```powershell
while ($true)
{
    Do-Something

    if ($Host.UI.RawUI.KeyAvailable)
    {
        break
    }
}
```

But it struck me that we would ideally be able to do something like this:

```powershell
$event = Register-EngineEvent -SourceIdentifier PowerShell.OnIdle -Action { Do-Something }
Read-Host
Unregister-Event -SubscriptionId $event.ID
```

While this essentially works with the PSReadLine prompt, it doesn't work with `Read-Host` (engine idle events aren't processed while waiting on `Read-Host`). Adding idle event processing on `Read-Host` might be a nice enhancement in PowerShell.

